From: Armbian <info@armbian.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] pinctrl: mvebu: armada-37xx: init info->dev before devm_kzalloc

info->dev is uninitialized going into devm_kzalloc(), which crashes on boot
for armada_37xx once the driver uses devres (CONFIG_DEVRES=y, since u-boot
commit 217cf65). Set info->dev in probe before the first devm_ allocation.

Fixes an EspressoBin (Armada 3720) crash on boot with u-boot v2026.04. Taken
from the quiseleve/espressobin-bootloader (bschnei ebu-bootloader) devres.patch;
still absent upstream as of v2026.07 / master.

Signed-off-by: Igor Pecovnik <igor@armbian.com>
---
 drivers/pinctrl/mvebu/pinctrl-armada-37xx.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/pinctrl/mvebu/pinctrl-armada-37xx.c b/drivers/pinctrl/mvebu/pinctrl-armada-37xx.c
--- a/drivers/pinctrl/mvebu/pinctrl-armada-37xx.c
+++ b/drivers/pinctrl/mvebu/pinctrl-armada-37xx.c
@@ -720,6 +720,8 @@ static int armada_37xx_pinctrl_probe(struct udevice *dev)
 		return -ENODEV;
 	}

+	info->dev = dev;
+
 	/*
 	 * we allocate functions for number of pins and hope there are
 	 * fewer unique functions than pins available
